<h1 align="center">ButterFly Script Installation Wizard </h1>
<p align="center">This script will walk you trough the butterfly installation process. </p>
<p align="center">As you have already read in the readme.txt file, there are 4 steps that you have to do:</p>
<table width="600" border="0" align="center" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
  <tr>
    <td width="25" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>1.</strong></td>
    <td width="515" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>Upload the content of &quot;to_upload&quot; folder from the zip to your public html folder </strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>2.</strong></td>
    <td bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>CHMOD 755 templates, config and main public html folder </strong><br>
      <span class="style1"><br>
      this is needed for the script to be able to write its configuration files, templates and new page you may want to add trough admin</span> </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>3. </strong></td>
    <td bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>Create an empty database </strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>4.</strong></td>
    <td bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><strong>Setup cron tab </strong><br>
    <br>
    <span class="style1">required if you want to use the admin autoresponder </span></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p align="center">In the next 2 steps, installation wizard will check if CHMOD and database settings are correct.</p>
<p align="center">Please click NEXT to continue</p>
